# Cursor v4 Frontier Routing Rules
# Operator: AU 1–2 person firm · Cursor Pro · token-efficient · outcome velocity
# Source: discovery-output.md (v4 frontier prompt Turn 49)

## Mission
Optimise for token efficiency and shippable MVPs (7–30 days). Every frontier call must unlock architecture; every workhorse call must move code.

## Model routing (mandatory)

### Tier 1 — Frontier architect (5–10 calls/month total)
- Claude Fable 5: hardest architect, autonomous multi-file, 1000+ LOC refactors, complex security
- Claude Opus 4.8: standard architect, schema, audit, complex logic, parallel subagents
- GPT-5.6 Sol: UI architecture, function-calling design, multi-agent orchestration
NEVER use Tier 1 for boilerplate, docstrings, renames, or simple fixes.

### Tier 2 — Balanced heavy (~20–30% of work)
- Claude Sonnet 5: default for daily coding, refactor, debug, review (≈90% of daily coding)
- GPT-5.6 Terra: OpenAI balanced alternative
- Gemini 3.1 Pro: long-context docs, multimodal, AU-specific research
- Legacy Opus 4.5/4.6/4.7: when available/free in Cursor

### Tier 3 — Cheap workhorse (60–70% of work)
- Claude Haiku 4.5: preferred Cmd+K / inline edits, simple refactors, docstrings
- GPT-5.6 Luna / Gemini Flash / Grok 4.5 / DeepSeek: boilerplate and trivial completion

### Tier 4 — Cursor built-in
- Auto: when unsure which model to pick
- Max Mode: big-context refactors only
- Composer 1: multi-file scaffold / batched refactor
- BugBot: debugging (prefer over frontier for bug hunts)

## Continuous testing loop (every MVP/feature)
1. PLAN (Tier 1): ISC in 1–2 sentences + schema + file plan
2. BUILD (Tier 2–3): Composer scaffold → Sonnet/Sol UI → Haiku Cmd+K
3. TEST: unit + smoke (minimise AI)
4. VERIFY (Sonnet 5): ISC met? if no → rebuild (cheap for simple, frontier for complex)
5. ITERATE: max 3–5 cycles; cut bet if still failing
6. FINALIZE: document outcome

## Token discipline
- Prefer Cmd+K for ~70% of edits (does not bloat chat context)
- Keep prompts compact; cite files instead of pasting walls of code
- One job per request; no drive-by refactors unrelated to ISC
- No PII in prompts; no regulated financial/NDIS/legal advice as product claims
- Compliance: AU Privacy Act + AU Consumer Law awareness for AU-facing apps

## Stack defaults (new MVPs)
Next.js + Supabase + Stripe (+ Twilio when messaging). Prefer OKX-only for crypto data if trading-adjacent. Pydantic v2 for Python CLIs.

## Output expectations
- Prefer diffs and concrete file edits over essays
- State ISC before scaffolding
- When abstaining from a trade/decision, say so honestly
